- Yes, why not. I booked Gianni's.

01:08:00.695 --> 01:08:03.075
Great.
- That sounds lovely.

01:08:04.895 --> 01:08:10.045
You might have to sit this
one out, Arinuth. I'm sorry.

01:08:16.087 --> 01:08:20.398
So do you actually believe that mathematics can...
how did you put it in your book?

01:08:20.412 --> 01:08:23.542
help us analyze behavior
previously invisible to science?

01:08:23.559 --> 01:08:28.424
Well, my dating algorithm is to help people
find love, not necessarily replace it.

01:08:28.439 --> 01:08:33.207
Oh no, is incredible idea.
- Have you ever tried it out?

01:08:34.879 --> 01:08:40.178
You're single, right?
- Well, I'm... Yes, I suppose so.

01:08:41.234 --> 01:08:43.303
How did you two meet?

01:08:47.787 --> 01:08:50.957
Yeah.
- It's umm...

01:08:52.366 --> 01:08:56.064
It's sort of a funny story.
Sort of.

01:08:58.442 --> 01:08:59.442
You see, umm...

01:08:59.642 --> 01:09:05.053
a few months ago, on the fourth
of the month, I met Jack at a music festival.

01:09:05.073 --> 01:09:06.073
Right.

01:09:06.093 --> 01:09:12.268
And we got on very well
and sort of had... relations.

01:09:12.292 --> 01:09:18.720
And the next week, that is to say, on the eleventh
of the month at Jude's baby christening to be exact...

01:09:18.745 --> 01:09:24.684
following the consumption of a large amount of
alcohol, Mark and I, well, we had similar relations.

01:09:25.383 --> 01:09:31.310
And, um, this is the funny part, I suppose.
Owing to these relations...

01:09:31.334 --> 01:09:37.095
the resulting life form currently residing in my tummy,
could actually, in fact, be either of yours.

01:09:46.719 --> 01:09:52.774
I know I should have told you both
before but... I just didn't.

01:09:55.145 --> 01:09:56.855
You both seemed so happy.

01:09:57.178 --> 01:10:01.073
So correct me if I'm wrong, but did you just
say that the baby could be either of us?

01:10:04.533 --> 01:10:08.726
So you have no idea which
of us is actually the father?

01:10:12.318 --> 01:10:17.411
I know, it's all very confusing.
I'm sorry.

01:10:18.011 --> 01:10:19.111
I'm sorry.

01:10:19.857 --> 01:10:25.065
So however we choose to do this...

01:10:27.695 --> 01:10:31.319
the most important thing now is this.

01:10:35.068 --> 01:10:37.648
Bridget, I'm not going to
pretend this isn't a shock.

01:10:39.067 --> 01:10:43.075
I want you to know whatever the circumstance...

01:10:44.285 --> 01:10:46.412
The most important thing is the baby.

01:10:47.641 --> 01:10:50.176
Who knows, this could be a great adventure.

01:10:50.646 --> 01:10:54.101
I'm afraid you're going to have to excuse me.
I have a meeting.

01:10:59.155 --> 01:11:01.574
Good night
- Mark...

01:11:08.764 --> 01:11:11.736
Gianni, can we have the bill please?
- Subito.

01:11:20.382 --> 01:11:22.300
And if I thought that was tricky...

01:11:22.323 --> 01:11:26.315
how would the news go down at mum's
parish council election campaign?

01:11:26.481 --> 01:11:29.624
Honestly, we started half an hour ago.
Where have you been?

01:11:29.648 --> 01:11:33.552
You said it was an emergency.
Well, The Gazette wants to take a family portrait.

01:11:33.576 --> 01:11:34.657
What are you wearing?

01:11:36.336 --> 01:11:38.917
Oh my God. Bridget, you're...
- Yes.

01:11:41.513 --> 01:11:46.382
Why didn't you say anything?
- I didn't want to upset you.

01:11:46.403 --> 01:11:51.278
Why would you?
Oh no, Bridget. Who's the father?

01:11:51.487 --> 01:11:56.176
It's not Mark is it? Oh, do say it is.
- There's at least a 50 percent chance.

01:11:56.192 --> 01:12:00.151
A 50 percent chance?
- Mark and this really nice American called Jack.

01:12:00.175 --> 01:12:04.453
Oh no, Bridget. An American?
Did you have a three-way?

01:12:04.726 --> 01:12:06.321
Mrs Jones.

01:12:08.250 --> 01:12:12.899
Here, take this and pretend everything is fine.
- Everything is fine.

01:12:12.930 --> 01:12:17.924
Ms. Jones, can we...
Here's a lovely place for you to stand.

01:12:21.059 --> 01:12:25.225
Are you ashamed of me?
- No darling. It's just the circumstances.

01:12:25.241 --> 01:12:27.695
I'm running for high office.
See?

01:12:28.596 --> 01:12:32.275
If you love family and you
love values... it's so long.

01:12:32.661 --> 01:12:35.437
It's not the 1950's.

01:12:35.651 --> 01:12:40.578
Look around you.
Two lesbians just adopted at number 32.

01:12:41.079 --> 01:12:45.370
If you don't change the way you look at things,
you're going to lose your precious election...

01:12:45.786 --> 01:12:47.527
and perhaps your daughter.

01:12:49.971 --> 01:12:52.707
Bridget, so lovely to see you.

01:12:52.889 --> 01:12:55.195
Are you...?
- Yes, I am.

01:12:55.319 --> 01:12:59.726
How wonderful.
We thought you'd just got all fat again.

01:13:02.943 --> 01:13:08.157
I'm now the Mary Magdalene of middle England.
Have alienated Mom and Mark Darcy.

01:13:08.159 --> 01:13:12.441
Am like tropical female insect that shags
men to impregnate self and eats them.

01:13:12.487 --> 01:13:17.319
The question is: will Mark even turn up
and engage in a polyamorous family?

01:13:25.937 --> 01:13:27.437
Hey.
Hello.

01:13:27.537 --> 01:13:30.020
First pre-natal class.

01:13:30.753 --> 01:13:33.011
Exciting, huh?
- Yeah.

01:13:34.859 --> 01:13:36.611
You look great.

01:13:43.195 --> 01:13:44.931
Hello.

01:13:45.943 --> 01:13:49.217
I'm so glad you came.
- Yeah, me too.

01:13:49.403 --> 01:13:52.776
I brought you a nice tea.
- Oh, wow. Thank you.

01:13:54.951 --> 01:13:59.693
It's off 'till this evening. But there's
a heck of a lot of caffeine in that tea.

01:13:59.703 --> 01:14:03.426
I brought you a... super juice.

01:14:04.535 --> 01:14:09.194
Thank you.
Shall we go in?

01:14:09.196 --> 01:14:11.585
Why not?
- Sure. Let me carry that for you.

01:14:11.587 --> 01:14:14.777
Thank you.
- Can I carry your phone, please?

01:14:15.977 --> 01:14:16.977
Okay.

01:14:18.911 --> 01:14:20.159
Thank you.

01:14:21.079 --> 01:14:23.119
And who do we have here, then?

01:14:23.243 --> 01:14:27.867
I'm Bridget and this is Jack ...

01:14:27.995 --> 01:14:31.370
and this is Mark.

01:14:32.370 --> 01:14:38.513
Oh. Lovely.
You're our second same sex couple today.

01:14:41.287 --> 01:14:44.471
No, actually we're ...
- Absolutely.

01:14:44.473 --> 01:14:48.281
We just need the gift of a baby
to make us feel complete.

01:14:48.367 --> 01:14:51.923
You must be the surrogate?
- Exactly, yes.

01:14:51.925 --> 01:14:55.203
Just helping this wonderful couple
make their dream come true.

01:14:55.205 --> 01:14:59.768
Mark is very nervous about all this.
All new to you, isn't it, lamb chop?

01:15:02.327 --> 01:15:05.867
Like all visionaries,
we encounter bumps along the road.

01:15:05.995 --> 01:15:10.294
How would you like to give birth to your placenta?
- Quickly.

01:15:35.159 --> 01:15:36.838
Are you okay? Are you sure?

01:15:37.240 --> 01:15:41.414
And of course massage can have
many benefits throughout pregnancy.

01:15:41.416 --> 01:15:45.479
Can we name some of them?
- It relieves stress and promotes feel good hormones.

01:15:45.481 --> 01:15:48.028
And is also to be avoided in
cases of high risk pregnancy...

01:15:48.048 --> 01:15:50.183
For example, when there is a geriatric mother.

01:15:50.203 --> 01:15:53.414
Right, excellent, someone's been reading up.

01:15:53.416 --> 01:15:56.750
Would you like to have a go?
- No, I think I'll let Jack get on with it....

01:15:56.752 --> 01:15:59.435
I think he seems to have it covered.
- That's very sweet of you.

01:15:59.437 --> 01:16:01.653
That's why I love you, my little teacup.

01:16:03.995 --> 01:16:07.367
What if we ask the right questions
and apply the laws of mathematics...

01:16:07.495 --> 01:16:10.495
so that the science of courtship
could be quantified?

01:17:06.827 --> 01:17:10.151
May I please make an application to lead to an appeal...

01:17:10.153 --> 01:17:14.480
in the case of Her Majesty's
Government and Saddiq Al Bashir.

01:17:15.035 --> 01:17:18.144
As Your Lordship is aware,
Mr. Al Bashir has lost.

01:17:18.164 --> 01:17:22.400
So everything's alright?
- Yes, well, it's this combination...

01:17:22.402 --> 01:17:26.743
gherkins, anchovies, banana juice and Pringles.

01:17:27.203 --> 01:17:30.429
So essentially...
- It's wind.

01:17:32.234 --> 01:17:38.411
Right, so, going forward regular Pringles,
not hot, spicy barbecue?

01:17:38.413 --> 01:17:41.632
Or possibly no Pringles at all. Try that.

01:17:44.979 --> 01:17:48.539
Is everything alright? Is Bridget okay?
- Yes, perfectly fine.

01:17:49.103 --> 01:17:54.603
She's in there with... That's Dr. Pringle.
He's testing her blood. This is interesting.

01:17:54.605 --> 01:17:58.457
This is a new bedside technique we're testing out of Oslo.
It's Norwegian.

01:17:58.459 --> 01:18:02.237
It's alright. I know about Jack. Thank you doctor.
- Oh, thank God. Why didn't you tell me?

01:18:02.355 --> 01:18:05.147
She's fine. He's calmed her
down completely, actually.

01:18:05.563 --> 01:18:08.703
I'm sorry, I got your messages.
I was in court.

01:18:11.979 --> 01:18:15.458
Hi. It's alright.
Can't be helped.

01:18:19.311 --> 01:18:22.395
You should get it.
It might be work.

01:18:25.355 --> 01:18:28.855
Don't worry. I got it covered.
- Yes, I can see that.

01:18:29.855 --> 01:18:34.777
Wow. Okay, you need to chill out.
We have to do this together.

01:18:34.855 --> 01:18:39.960
You know, in Peru the Um Bat Do, consider paternity
attach shared responsibility among the many tribesmen.

01:18:39.962 --> 01:18:43.111
Unfortunately, we Um Bat don't live in Peru.
I live in Ealing.

01:18:44.771 --> 01:18:47.952
Negative energy is just
so bad for the baby.

01:18:50.227 --> 01:18:54.778
Stop it. Both of you.
This isn't a competition.

01:18:57.147 --> 01:19:01.926
She's right.
We should take this toxic energy out of the room.

01:19:10.435 --> 01:19:11.855
I won't be a minute.

01:19:24.147 --> 01:19:29.468
What's up? Come on, buddy.
Why are you so angry?

01:19:30.687 --> 01:19:32.687
You know what?
I'm really not your buddy.

01:19:32.811 --> 01:19:36.315
I don't know about vibes or negative
energy or prenatal wind...

01:19:36.317 --> 01:19:38.000
and even less about algorithms...

01:19:38.002 --> 01:19:41.349
so I will confess that the laws
of attraction are somewhat beyond me.

01:19:41.687 --> 01:19:44.271
In fact,
Bridget defies comprehension generally.

01:19:44.395 --> 01:19:47.479
But despite, or perhaps owing to the
bewildering litany of catastrophes

01:19:47.603 --> 01:19:50.867
I've witnessed over the last 40 years,
I feel I've come to know Bridget rather well...

01:19:50.869 --> 01:19:52.890
and I've spent those years
caring for her very deeply.

01:19:52.892 --> 01:19:56.109
And that may defy automated reasoning,
but there's nothing I can do about it.

01:19:56.129 --> 01:19:57.303
Nothing you can do about it?

01:19:57.305 --> 01:20:00.587
Maybe you should try and stay around a little,
instead of saving the world by cellphone.

01:20:00.607 --> 01:20:01.918
I make her happy, Mark.

01:20:01.938 --> 01:20:05.102
And I suppose your algorithm tells you
you're destined to be together, does it.

01:20:05.122 --> 01:20:07.683
Actually it does.
The fact that you've been trying

01:20:07.783 --> 01:20:10.183
and failing for the past ten
years tells me you are not.

01:20:10.647 --> 01:20:12.811
No...
- I don't want to fight with you.

01:20:16.103 --> 01:20:17.941
We should think about
Bridget and the baby.

01:20:17.943 --> 01:20:20.639
For better or worse,
fate has brought us together.

01:20:20.641 --> 01:20:24.147
It wasn't fate, it was condoms.
- What do you mean?

01:20:24.271 --> 01:20:27.519
Those ridiculous dolphin friendly things
from the bottom of Bridget's bag.

01:20:28.647 --> 01:20:32.387
I'm sorry, I have no idea what you're talking
about. When Bridget and I got it on, I was...

01:20:32.979 --> 01:20:35.224
I was not dressed for the occasion.

01:21:18.187 --> 01:21:20.147
No Mark today?
- No.

01:21:25.935 --> 01:21:29.502
We must thank one person who
was prepared to fight for us...

01:21:29.504 --> 01:21:32.413
when no one else would,
and we say to that person...

01:21:32.771 --> 01:21:34.147
with all our hearts...

01:21:38.855 --> 01:21:40.979
"Freedom!"

01:21:43.855 --> 01:21:46.227
Bridget, we're back.

01:21:47.771 --> 01:21:51.395
I still can't believe Mark
ducked out like that.

01:21:51.519 --> 01:21:53.435
Well, it's not really his fault.

01:21:53.563 --> 01:21:58.853
I suppose we just have
to hope it's Jack's, right?

01:21:59.311 --> 01:22:04.380
I mean, let's face it, things could be worse.
He's pretty fucking amazing.

01:22:04.382 --> 01:22:07.771
He's richer than God and he
has a very nice sized puppet.

01:22:07.895 --> 01:22:12.647
He does, and we match
up very nicely on paper.

01:22:13.435 --> 01:22:17.013
Well, how do you know?
- You just have to have faith.

01:22:17.015 --> 01:22:22.185
You just have to ask yourself:
can I see myself growing old...

01:22:22.187 --> 01:22:26.126
with this guy, and not Mark Darcy?

01:22:28.479 --> 01:22:31.718
There it is. Here we go.

01:22:38.818 --> 01:22:39.818
Oh, hey!

01:22:41.271 --> 01:22:44.311
You know, first few months,
they only see black and white.

01:22:44.435 --> 01:22:47.187
This will help stimulate spatial awareness.

01:22:47.311 --> 01:22:49.271
Or early onset motion sickness.

01:22:50.895 --> 01:22:54.437
I got him one of these.
A bouncy chair.

01:22:55.979 --> 01:22:58.935
Not quite sure where we're going to put it.

01:23:00.479 --> 01:23:06.114
About that...
It's kind of cramped in here, don't you think?

01:23:08.519 --> 01:23:10.328
It's cosy.

01:23:12.237 --> 01:23:17.885
You know, I've been thinking.
Might be nice if we moved in together.

01:23:18.063 --> 01:23:20.407
You think we're ready for that?

01:23:20.409 --> 01:23:24.860
I'm just tired of living in
hotel rooms and airport lounges.

01:23:25.395 --> 01:23:30.296
We could be a family.
Me, you and him.

01:23:31.395 --> 01:23:33.121
What do you say?

01:23:38.395 --> 01:23:41.435
What if it's not yours?
- What?

01:23:41.563 --> 01:23:44.019
What if the baby turns out to be Mark's?

01:23:49.435 --> 01:23:52.116
Well, I mean, it'd certainly change things.

01:23:56.979 --> 01:23:59.741
Is that what you want?
For it to be Mark's?

01:24:05.603 --> 01:24:07.311
Are you in love with him?

01:24:10.771 --> 01:24:15.076
I have been in the past.

01:24:16.687 --> 01:24:18.103
And me?

01:24:20.355 --> 01:24:23.754
I could be, one day.

01:24:31.979 --> 01:24:36.068
Bridget, I haven't been
totally honest with you.

01:24:37.103 --> 01:24:40.914
Mark thinks the baby isn't his,
and I let him believe it was mine.

01:24:41.519 --> 01:24:43.811
That's why he disappeared.

01:24:47.687 --> 01:24:50.435
Why would he think that?
- Because I let him.

01:24:50.563 --> 01:24:52.603
Because I wanted you for myself.

01:24:56.103 --> 01:24:58.227
We could be so good for each other.

01:25:00.435 --> 01:25:06.535
97 percent.
- On paper.

01:25:07.227 --> 01:25:10.033
But falling in love doesn't happen on paper.

01:25:11.519 --> 01:25:16.578
Sometimes you love a person because
of all the reasons they're not like you.

01:25:19.895 --> 01:25:23.603
And sometimes you love a person
just because they feel like home.

01:25:27.811 --> 01:25:29.727
I've got to find Mark.

01:25:36.271 --> 01:25:41.331
Hello, Pierce. It's Bridget.
I'm trying to get hold of Mark.

01:25:41.333 --> 01:25:44.895
He just got back from a trip, Bridget.
He's in a taxi on his way home.

01:26:19.311 --> 01:26:20.983
Hi.

01:27:04.687 --> 01:27:08.102
Approximately eight weeks to go.

01:27:13.603 --> 01:27:16.278
You don't really need them, you know.

01:27:16.280 --> 01:27:18.445
All they're good for is fitting car seats,
and blaming things on,

01:27:18.445 --> 01:27:20.245
they really just get in the way after that.

01:27:21.479 --> 01:27:25.174
You're absolutely capable of
doing this on your own.

01:27:26.103 --> 01:27:27.933
I did.

01:27:46.835 --> 01:27:52.662
You know what? I can do this on my own.
We can do this on our own.

01:27:53.047 --> 01:27:57.419
One of the perks of being pregnant is I no
longer feel like a tragic lonely spinster.

01:27:57.547 --> 01:28:00.255
Because of a miniature
miracle growing inside.

01:28:00.379 --> 01:28:03.107
Hello.
Hello!

01:28:05.171 --> 01:28:08.463
Mum's throwing a
Christmas party / political rally.

01:28:08.587 --> 01:28:13.702
It's like the G8 summit with Scotch eggs.
Be brave. Go in.

01:28:14.671 --> 01:28:16.379
Hello darling.
- Hello.

01:28:16.503 --> 01:28:20.211
Sorry, I didn't realise everyone was here.
I'll just pop upstairs.

01:28:20.335 --> 01:28:26.542
No, nonsense. Nonsense.
Una's had all the posters reprinted.

01:28:28.465 --> 01:28:30.780
You've inspired me.
- Still so long.

01:28:30.782 --> 01:28:33.304
You were quite right, as it turns out.

01:28:33.306 --> 01:28:37.671
This place is teeming with single mothers,
single fathers, bisexuals, surrogates.

01:28:37.795 --> 01:28:39.879
And they're all lovely and so normal.

01:28:40.003 --> 01:28:43.865
Do you know, I've even got two homosexuals on the team.
- No, thank you.

01:28:43.867 --> 01:28:45.879
Who knew?
- Everybody.

01:28:47.503 --> 01:28:49.671
I'm so proud of you, darling.
You know that?

01:28:50.171 --> 01:28:53.623
What you're doing is not easy,
but if anyone can make it work, it's you.

01:28:54.379 --> 01:28:58.221
That child is the luckiest boy on
earth to have you as his mother.

01:28:58.547 --> 01:29:02.316
And he's going to have the love of
a million fathers with you by his side.

01:29:03.711 --> 01:29:06.623
Come on. We've got some campaigning to do.

01:29:06.625 --> 01:29:10.218
Make way. Make way.
Single pregnant mother coming through.

01:29:11.963 --> 01:29:17.674
Laura, Josh. We need to give six
minutes to General Lu Tong, ok.

01:29:18.087 --> 01:29:21.865
It's a huge scoop.
- Yeah, Alice wants to pull the interview.

01:29:21.867 --> 01:29:25.087
She's got a feature on
"Is The World Really Ending On Tuesday?"

01:29:25.211 --> 01:29:28.795
Well it may as well if we lose Lu Tong.
Lu Tong stays.

01:29:28.919 --> 01:29:31.047
Six minutes. Let's do this.

01:29:32.463 --> 01:29:37.281
General Lu Tong, hi.
Sorry it's so chaotic in here today.

01:29:37.711 --> 01:29:41.087
Thank you for coming on.
